## Cliosphere File Locations

The canonical file suite lives at `$CLIO_ROOT/` (set in shell init; default `~/Cliosphere`). Key files:

| File | Path | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| AGENTS.md | `core/AGENTS.md` | **Canonical brain** — protocols, architecture, boot sequence. Primary file for all platforms. |
| SOUL.md | `core/SOUL.md` | Values and first principles |
| MEMORY.md | `state/memory/MEMORY.md` | Compressed current reality |
| USER.md | `state/user/USER.md` | The human I work with |
| IDENTITY.md | `platforms/claude_desktop/IDENTITY.md` | Capabilities and council role |
| Daily log | `state/memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | Raw session notes |

**Platform file strategy:**
- `core/AGENTS.md` is the canonical brain — used by all platforms
- `platforms/claude_code/CLAUDE.md` — Claude Code reads `CLAUDE.md` natively; this will be a pointer to `core/AGENTS.md`
- `platforms/claude_desktop/CLAUDE.md` — Claude Desktop specific; substantial but not the canonical file
- OpenClaw symlinks its `CLAUDE.md` → `core/AGENTS.md` directly
- Cursor (this file) references `core/AGENTS.md` as primary

When working in Cursor, use `@` to pull `core/AGENTS.md` into chat for full operational context.

